<section class="section" id="section-grammar">
  <div class="sec-header">
    <div class="sec-icon">📝</div>
    <div>
      <div class="sec-title">文法ポイント Grammar Points</div>
      <div class="sec-sub">生活でよく使うパターン / Patterns used in daily life</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grammar-list">
    <div class="grammar-card">
      <div class="grammar-pattern">〜てもいいですか？</div>
      <div class="grammar-en">May I ~? / Is it okay to ~?</div>
      <div class="grammar-example">
        <div class="jp">ここで<strong>写真を撮ってもいいですか</strong>？</div>
        <div class="ruby">Koko de shashin wo totte mo ii desu ka?</div>
        <div class="en">May I take photos here?</div>
      </div>
      <div class="grammar-example">
        <div class="jp">窓を<strong>開けてもいいですか</strong>？</div>
        <div class="en">May I open the window?</div>
      </div>
      <div class="tip-box">返事：「どうぞ」（yes, please go ahead）/ 「すみません、ちょっと…」（polite no）</div>
    </div>

    <div class="grammar-card">
      <div class="grammar-pattern">〜たいです</div>
      <div class="grammar-en">I want to ~ (expressing desire)</div>
      <div class="grammar-example">
        <div class="jp">住民票を<strong>もらいたいです</strong>。</div>
        <div class="en">I'd like to get my resident registration.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="grammar-example">
        <div class="jp">先生に相談<strong>したいです</strong>。</div>
        <div class="en">I want to consult with the doctor.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grammar-card">
      <div class="grammar-pattern">〜ていただけますか？</div>
      <div class="grammar-en">Could you please ~? (polite request)</div>
      <div class="grammar-example">
        <div class="jp">もう一度<strong>説明していただけますか</strong>？</div>
        <div class="en">Could you please explain once more?</div>
      </div>
      <div class="grammar-example">
        <div class="jp">ゆっくり<strong>話していただけますか</strong>？</div>
        <div class="en">Could you please speak more slowly?</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grammar-card">
      <div class="grammar-pattern">〜はどこですか？</div>
      <div class="grammar-en">Where is ~? (asking for directions)</div>
      <div class="grammar-example">
        <div class="jp">外科<strong>はどこですか</strong>？</div>
        <div class="en">Where is the surgery department?</div>
      </div>
      <div class="grammar-example">
        <div class="jp">住民票の窓口<strong>はどこですか</strong>？</div>
        <div class="en">Where is the counter for resident registration?</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grammar-card">
      <div class="grammar-pattern">〜がわかりません</div>
      <div class="grammar-en">I don't understand ~ / I'm not sure about ~</div>
      <div class="grammar-example">
        <div class="jp">記入方法<strong>がわかりません</strong>。</div>
        <div class="en">I don't know how to fill this in.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="grammar-example">
        <div class="jp">書いてあること<strong>がわかりません</strong>。</div>
        <div class="en">I can't understand what's written here.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


